@rithviknishad 
I have migrated the ActiveProjects component to use octokit but I have no way of testing if it works. The code is like this:
```
const data: GraphQLOrgActiveProjectsResponse = await octokit.graphql(
    `
      query getIssues($org: String!, $labelsFilter: String!) {
        organization(login: $org) {
          repositories(first: 100, orderBy: {field: PUSHED_AT, direction: DESC}) {
            edges {
              node {
                name
                issues(first: 100, states: OPEN, labels: [$labelsFilter]) {
                  edges {
                    node {
                      title
                      body
                      url
                      createdAt
                      updatedAt
                      author {
                        login
                      },
                      labels(first: 5) {
                        edges {
                          node {
                            name
                          }
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    `,
    {
      org: env.NEXT_PUBLIC_GITHUB_ORG,
      labelsFilter,
    },
  );
```
Right now it only shows "No active projects" locally since GITHUB_PAT is empty.

